    h5.Article-Heading6 Renaming of #[code NARROWEST_SCREEN_WIDTH_UNIT] Constant

    p.Article-Paragraph.
      #[+Term--YDID Constant] #[+ImportantEntity__Code--YDID NARROWEST_SCREEN_WIDTH_UNIT] has been renamed to
        #[+ImportantEntity__Code--YDID NARROWEST_SCREEN_WIDTH_UNIT--YDF].

    dl.Article-DescriptionList

      dt Reason
      dd.
        To significantly reduce the probability of name conflict, the #[+ImportantEntity__Code--YDID --YDF]
          #[+Term--YDID verndor postfix] has been appended.

      dt Changes in your code will required if
      dd.
        Your code has explicit usages of #[+ImportantEntity__Code--YDID NARROWEST_SCREEN_WIDTH_UNIT]
          #[+Term--YDID constant].

      dt Migration
      dd.
        Using the appropriate functionality of your code editor or IDE, replace all occurrences of
          #[+ImportantEntity__Code--YDID NARROWEST_SCREEN_WIDTH_UNIT] with
          #[+ImportantEntity__Code--YDID mustThrowErrorIfElementNotFoundOrMatchesAreMultiple]
          in all #[+Term--YDID Stylus files] of your project.
        For example, in #[+ImportantEntity--YDID IntelliJ IDEA] family IDEs, such functionality could be invoked
          by #[+SecondaryEntity__Code--YDID Ctrl + Shift + R] as default.


