    h6.Article-Heading6 Changes two-level object #[code TemporaryHighlighting]

    ul.Article-UnorderedList

      li.
        Object has been renamed to #[+ImportantEntity__Code--YDID TemporarySemitransparentHighlighting--YDF].

      li.
        Now the ultrashort properties line #[+SecondaryEntity__Code--YDID o25], which meaning could not&nbsp;be understood
          without the documentation or checking of the output #[+Term--YDID CSS code] has been replaces with meaningful,
          such as #[+SecondaryEntity__Code--YDID opacity25Percent].

    dl.Article-DescriptionList

      dt Reasons
      dd

        ul.Article-UnorderedList

          li The «transparent» word has been added to increase the unambiguity.

          li.
            To #[+Term--YDID vendor postfix] #[+ImportantEntity__Code--YDID --YDF] has been added to the
              to significantly reduce the name conflict probability.

          li.
            The #[+Term--YDID properties] of the second level has been renamed because basically #[+Keyword--YDID all]
              libraries of #[+ImportantEntity--YDID Yamato Daiwa] vendor does&nbsp;#[+Keyword--YDID not] accept the names
              which meaning could&nbsp;not&nbsp;be understood wihtout the documentation, so now this rule has been
              applied to #[+ImportantEntity--YDID TemporarySemitransparentHighlighting--YDF] object even though it
              is&nbsp;#[+Keyword--YDID not]&nbsp;intended to be used in production code.

      dt Changes of your code will require if
      dd.
        You, contrary to the recommendation to not&nbsp;use this object in the clean copy of stylesheet did it,
          or you has updated the #[+ImportantEntity--YDID YDF] during the writing of the draft #[+Term--YDID CSS code]
          where used the #[+ImportantEntity--YDID TemporaryHighlighting] #[+Term--YDID object].

      dt Migration
      dd

        p.Article-Paragraph.
          Using the appropriate functionality of your code editor or IDE, execute the following replacements in
            all #[+Term--YDID Stylus files].

        ul.Article-UnorderedList
          li.
            #[+ImportantEntity__Code--YDID TemporaryHighlighting] ➝
