    dl.Article-DescriptionList

      dt Why has been replaced to configuration object
      dd

        p.Article-Paragraph.
          The #[+Term--YDID variables] had too common names and nothing has indicated that they are coming from
            #[+ImportantEntity--YDID YDF].
          To solve the last these problems, it was possible to append the #[+Term--YDID vendor postfix] to
            #[+Term--YDID variables] (for example, #[+SecondaryEntity__Code--YDID MAIN_SANS_SERIF_FONT_STACK] could
            become to #[+SecondaryEntity__Code--YDID MAIN_SANS_SERIF_FONT_STACK--YDF] this way), but the
            #[+Term--YDID object-type variable] is better for the storing of configuration.

      dt Changes of your code will require if
      dd You have #[+Keyword--YDID directly] used one or more of mentioned above #[+Term--YDID variables]

      dt Migration
      dd

        ul.Article-UnorderedList

          li.
            If you want to continue to use the #[+Term--YDID basic variables] with same names as previously, define
              them yourself with desired values.

          li.
            If you have #[+Keyword--YDID overridden] the #[+Term--YDID basic variables] then it is
              #[+Keyword--YDID required] to #[+Keyword--YDID override] the
              #[+ImportantEntity__Code--YDID YDF_Configuration] object #[+Keyword--YDID instead].

          li.
            If you are fine with usage of the #[+ImportantEntity__Code--YDID YDF_Configuration] object
              #[+Keyword--YDID instead] of the of the #[+Term--YDID basic variables], then replace the references
              to these #[+Term--YDID variables] with the accessing to the corresponding #[+Term--YDID properties] of the
              #[+ImportantEntity__Code--YDID YDF_Configuration] object.
            But please note that this #[+Term--YDID object] as it is clear from its name is intended for the
              configuration of the #[+ImportantEntity--YDID YDF] functionality and this library is just the utility
              in your project.
            So, if you have the unique design, then the settings related with this design recommended to define
              #[+Keyword--YDID independently] on #[+ImportantEntity--YDID YDF], and let
              #[+ImportantEntity__Code--YDID YDF_Configuration] #[+Term--YDID object properties] refers to the settings
              of your design.
